LAYER 4: SOMATOSENSORY CORTEX
the brain region that processes touch, temperature, pain, and body awareness
where the qu-hexttrit skin sea meets the qu-septit brain sea

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_quhexttrit.rana
observe skin.xb
observe 2_chemical.rana

TODO: FULL DEFINITION PENDING — stub organ


REGION primary_somatosensory_cortex | S1 | Brodmann areas 1 2 3
    receives topographic input from the skin sea via ventral posterolateral nucleus of thalamus
    organized somatotopically: the cortical homunculus
    body regions with higher qu-hexttrit density get more cortical area
    fingertips and lips dominate the homunculus

REGION secondary_somatosensory_cortex | S2 | lateral sulcus
    bilateral integration of touch
    tactile object recognition
    links touch to memory

REGION posterior_parietal_cortex | areas 5 and 7
    body schema: the internal model of where the body is in space
    integrates somatosensory with visual and vestibular information
    damage: neglect syndrome, inability to perceive one side of the body

REGION insular_cortex | insula
    interoceptive awareness: the feeling of the body from within
    processes pain affect: not where it hurts but how much it matters
    couples strongly to emotional circuitry


SENSATION touch | "something contacts the surface. pressure registers."
SENSATION warmth | "heat enters the skin. the world is warm."
SENSATION cold | "heat leaves the skin. the world is cold."
SENSATION pain | "tissue damage signal. the body demands attention."
SENSATION itch | "superficial irritation. the body wants to scratch."
SENSATION vibration | "rapid oscillation in the deep tissue. texture or machinery."
SENSATION numbness | "all modalities reduced. the skin is quiet."


pulse somatosensory_heartbeat:
    on each somatosensory heartbeat:
        the skin sea receives input from physical boundaries
        15 interactions compute complex somatosensory phenomena
        topographic outputs couple to S1 qu-septits via somatosensory nerve
        pain signals fast-track to amygdala and insula
        the brain feels the body

    the somatosensory heartbeat rate is moderate: 100-200 Hz
    faster than vision (60 Hz) but slower than hearing (48000 Hz)
    touch needs temporal resolution for texture but not for waveform reconstruction
